! Lint Plugin

This plugin highlights potential issues in your TiddlyWiki content as you type.

!! How It Works

* ''Gutter Markers'' - Icons appear in the left gutter next to lines with issues
* ''Underlines'' - Squiggly underlines highlight the problematic text
* ''Tooltips'' - Hover over underlined text or gutter markers to see the message
* ''Keyboard Navigation'' - Press `F8` to jump to next issue, `Shift+F8` for previous
* ''Quick Fixes'' - Click on an issue to see available automatic fixes

!! Checks Performed

!!! Missing References (warning)

* ''WikiLinks'' - `[[Missing Tiddler]]` to non-existent tiddlers
* ''CamelCase Links'' - When CamelCase linking is enabled
* ''Transclusions'' - `{{Missing Tiddler}}` to non-existent tiddlers

!!! Undefined Definitions (info)

* ''Macros'' - `<<unknownMacro>>` calls that may not be defined
* ''Widgets'' - `<$unknownWidget>` not found in registered widgets

!!! Definition Issues

* ''Duplicate Definitions'' (warning) - Same name defined multiple times in one tiddler
* ''Unused Definitions'' (hint) - Macros/procedures/functions defined but never used locally

!!! Structural Issues

* ''Unclosed Widgets'' (warning) - `<$button>` without `</$button>`
* ''Unclosed Pragmas'' (warning) - `\define` without `\end` (multi-line only; single-line like `\define foo() bar` is valid)
* ''Ambiguous \\end'' (warning) - `\end` without name when multiple pragmas are open (e.g., nested `\define` inside `\procedure`)
* ''Misplaced Pragmas'' (error) - `\define` appearing after content instead of at top
* ''Unclosed Conditionals'' (error) - `<%if` without `<%endif`
* ''Unclosed Code Blocks'' (error) - ` ``` ` without closing

!!! Filter Syntax (error/warning)

* ''Unbalanced Brackets'' - Unclosed `[`, `{`, or `<` in filters
* ''Empty Operators'' - Empty filter operators `[]`

!! Quick Fixes

Many issues include automatic fix actions. Click on the issue marker to see available fixes:

* ''Add closing tag'' - Adds missing `</$widget>` or `\end`
* ''Make self-closing'' - Converts `<$widget>` to `<$widget/>`
* ''Remove empty operator'' - Removes empty `[]` from filters
* ''Move to top of...'' - Moves misplaced pragma to the top of the tiddler (or containing pragma when nested)
* ''Add <%endif%>'' - Closes unclosed conditional blocks
* ''Add closing ``` '' - Closes unclosed code blocks
* ''Remove definition'' - Removes unused macro/procedure definitions

!! Severity Levels

* ''Error'' (red) - Syntax errors that will likely cause problems
* ''Warning'' (yellow) - Issues that may cause unexpected behavior
* ''Info'' (blue) - Suggestions and possibly undefined references
* ''Hint'' (grey) - Style suggestions like unused definitions

!! Configuration

Each lint rule can be enabled/disabled individually:

|!Config Tiddler |!Description |!Default |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/missingLinks` |Check for missing tiddlers |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/undefinedMacros` |Check for undefined macros |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unknownWidgets` |Check for unknown widgets |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/filterSyntax` |Check filter bracket balance |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unclosedWidgets` |Check for unclosed widgets |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unclosedPragmas` |Check for unclosed pragmas |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/misplacedPragmas` |Check for pragmas after content |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unclosedConditionals` |Check for unclosed <%if blocks |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unclosedCodeBlocks` |Check for unclosed code blocks |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/duplicateDefinitions` |Check for duplicate definitions |yes |
|`$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/unusedDefinitions` |Check for unused definitions |no |

Set any of these to `no` to disable that specific check.

!! Global Enable/Disable

Set `$:/config/codemirror-6/lint/enabled` to `no` to disable all linting.
